llect Team GB's solitary gold from the athletics meet.\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 1022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.577009560935982e-13, \"text\": \"Mancunian\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester\"}, {\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dame Kelly Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.442928566357003e-16, \"text\": \"Athens 2004\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4789456434684675e-15, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the final straight\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 903}, {\"ngram\": \"her hero\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletics meet\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1021}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Outside the stadium, Team GB found more luck withAlex Yee who produced a stunning finishto the men's triathlon - delayed by a day due to a polluted Seine - to emulate Alistair Brownlee as Britain's second Olympic champion in the sport.\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1045, \"end\": 1052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4789456434684675